license: "LicenseRef-DDSync-NonCommercial-1.0"

# Update these to match your GitHub release + Zenodo record:
version: "0.1.0"
date-released: "2026-02-14"
doi: "10.5281/zenodo.XXXXXXXX"  # <-- version DOI for this release

keywords:
  - seismology
  - earthquake relocation
  - double-difference
  - HypoDD
  - GrowClust
  - differential travel times
  - graph synchronization
  - robust estimation

abstract: >
  DDSync is a lightweight graph-based synchronization/denoising tool for HypoDD/GrowClust-style
  dt.cc differential travel-time observations. For each station–phase, it solves a weighted
  least-squares synchronization problem to recover self-consistent relative arrival-time potentials,
  provides residual-based pruning using MAD thresholds, supports optional Huber IRLS reweighting,
  and can export thetaStd-based uncertainty diagnostics for downstream weighting.

